{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Combining DNNs with LSTM can be used for predicting exam scores based on the student's demographic and academic history data, while LSTM is utilized to model the temporal dependencies in the academic history, DNNs are employed to analyze the demographic data.",
    "For producing the final prediction, the outputs of the LSTM and DNNs can be combined and input into another DNN Hien et al (2020), where it has achieved an accuracy of about 86.26%.",
    "In Prabowo et al (2021), DNNs (MLP) and LSTM are combined to process both tabular data (demographic and course information) using MLP and time-series data (academic and GPA) using LSTM.",
    "Another effective method for predicting student performance is combining DL techniques with either ML or Ensemble Learning or both of them.",
    "Deep Learning techniques, such as DNNs and LSTM, are well-suited to capture complex relationships in the data, while Machine Learning techniques, such as Random Forest (RF), Decision Tree (DT), Linear Regression (LR) and clustering, can be effective at handling high-dimensional data and capturing non-linear relationships."
  ],
